Reasoning: The paper deals with object skeleton detection in natural images using a CNN-based approach. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a deep learning model for predicting a two-dimensional vector field also involves machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the handling of background clutter, which is a common problem in graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on benchmark datasets involves multimedia (cs.MM).
